05,"age":78,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705207,"age":94,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705208,"age":96,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"John Amptyll was born in 1491, in London, England. He married Isabell in 1512. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 2 daughters. He died in his hometown, and was buried in London, England."},"et":{"1491–":"1491–Surnud","1492–Female":"1492–Surnud","1519–Female":"1519–Surnud","1513–1556":"1513–1556","1515–1574":"1515–1574","1517–Female":"1517–Surnud","1518–1581":"1518–1581","1520–Female":"1520–Surnud","1491–Male":"1491–Surnud","Cir 1515":"1515","Cir 1520":"1520","1581":"1581","1492":"1492","1491":"1491","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1513":"1513","1512":"1512","1556":"1556","about 1517":"umbes 1517","1587":"1587","1520":"1520","1585":"1585","1574":"1574","1519":"1519","1518":"1518","1517":"1517","1549":"1549","1515":"1515","London, Greater London, England":"London, England","London, London, England":"London, England","St Giles, Middlesex, England":"St Giles, Middlesex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","St Giles in the Fields, Middlesex, 